    "caption": "Tall, orange-patched, and able to dive deeper than a skyscraper is tall.",
    "shortDescription": "King penguins are the second-tallest penguins, with bright orange and yellow patches on their necks like a painted scarf. They dive incredibly deep — down to three hundred meters — hunting fish and squid in the cold Southern Ocean. A king penguin chick spends almost a whole year growing in its brown fluffy coat before it's old enough to swim. Fun fact: King penguins can dive deeper than most submarines go."
